00020 /* Unlike previous versions of this code, uint32 need not be exactly
00021    32 bits, merely 32 bits or more.  Choosing a data type which is 32
00022    bits instead of 64 is not important; speed is considerably more
00023    important.  ANSI guarantees that "unsigned long" will be big enough,
00024    and always using it seems to have few disadvantages.  */
00025 typedef unsigned long cvs_uint32;
00026 
00027 struct cvs_MD5Context {
00028         cvs_uint32 buf[4];
00029         cvs_uint32 bits[2];
00030         unsigned char in[64];
00031 };
00032

00035                            unsigned char const *buf, unsigned len));

00037                           struct cvs_MD5Context *context));
00038 void cvs_MD5Transform PROTO ((cvs_uint32 buf[4], const unsigned char in[64]));
